Belgian coach Paul Van Himst picked seven players  each from champions Anderlecht and runners-up Bruges here Tuesday in his squad   for the World Cup football finals in the United States from June 17 to July  17.
Belgium World Cup quad
Goalkeepers: Michel Preud'homme (Mechelen), Filip Dewilde (RSC  Anderlecht), Dany Verlinden (Bruges)
Defenders: Dirk Medved (Bruges), Georges Grun (AC Parma, Italy), Michel De  Wolf (RSC Anderlecht), Philippe Albert (RSC Anderlecht), Rudi Smidts  (Antwerp), Pascal Renier (Bruges), Vital Borkelmans (Bruges)
Midfield: Lorenzo Staelens (Bruges), Franky Van der Elst (Bruges), Eric  Van Meir (Charleroi), Danny Boffin (RSC Anderlecht), Stefan Van der Heyden  (Bruges), Enzo Scifo (AS Monaco, France), Marc Emmers (RSC Anderlecht)
Forwards: Marc Degryse (RSC Anderlecht), Josip Weber (Cercle Bruges), Luc  Nilis (RSC Anderlecht), Alexandre Czerniatynski (Mechelen), Marc Wilmots  (Standard Liege)
